Transient rapamycin treatment can increase lifespan and healthspan in 
middle-aged mice.

Bitto A(1), Ito TK(1), Pineda VV(1), LeTexier NJ(1), Huang HZ(1), Sutlief E(1), 
Tung H(1), Vizzini N(1), Chen B(1), Smith K(1), Meza D(1), Yajima M(2), Beyer 
RP(3), Kerr KF(4), Davis DJ(5), Gillespie CH(5), Snyder JM(6), Treuting PM(6), 
Kaeberlein M(1).

Author information:
(1)Department of Pathology, University of Washington, Seattle, United States.
(2)Vaccine and Infectious Disease Division, Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research 
Center, Seattle, United States.
(3)Department of Environmental and Occupational Health Sciences, University of 
Washington, Seattle, United States.
(4)Department of Biostatistics, University of Washington, Seattle, United 
States.
(5)Department of Veterinary Pathobiology, University of Missouri, Columbia, 
